result.text:
Tips on Chinese Visa Application III

Service choice up to applicants. Applicants can choose the type of counter service by themselves. For qualified visa applications, the processing period by the Embassy is usually 2 working days (for express application) and 4 working days (for regular application). VIP service is a third party service offered by the Visa Center. The content of the VIP service is subject to the Visa Center, and is NOT related to the issuance of visas by the Embassy or the processing time.

result.text:
Tips on Chinese Visa Application I

To further facilitate applicants applying Chinese visa from Chinese Embassy in India through Chinese Visa Application Service Center in New Delhi, several kind tips are reminded as follows:

Submit your applications anytime as needed. There is no daily quota anymore for visa application appointments by applicants from the Embassy's consular jurisdiction area. Applicants can make online appointments for submitting visa applications on any working day. Starting from November 20, 2023, the requirement for appointment will be removed and applicants can directly submit application documents at the Visa Center on any working day.
